  "response": "Here's a breakdown of the differences between basic, intermediate, and advanced WordPress websites:\n\nBasic WordPress Website:\n- Pre-designed template/theme\n- Limited customization\n- Simple page structure\n- Basic content (text, images)\n- No complex functionality\n- Minimal plugins\n- Standard blog or informational site\n- Low budget\n- Limited SEO optimization\n\nIntermediate WordPress Website:\n- Custom or premium theme\n- More advanced design customization\n- Multiple page templates\n- Enhanced visual design\n- Contact forms\n- Basic e-commerce capabilities\n- More advanced plugins\n- Some custom functionality\n- Better SEO optimization\n- Mobile responsiveness\n- Integration with social media\n- Basic security measures\n\nAdvanced WordPress Website:\n- Fully custom-designed theme\n- Unique, complex design\n- Advanced functionality\n- Custom post types\n- Advanced e-commerce solutions\n- Membership/subscription features\n- Complex user roles\n- Advanced security protocols\n- Custom APIs and integrations\n- Performance optimization\n- Advanced SEO strategies\n- Multilingual support\n- Complex database interactions\n- Custom plugin development\n- Advanced analytics\n- Scalable infrastructure\n- Enterprise-level features\n\nEach level represents increasing complexity, investment, and potential for sophisticated web solutions.",
